data.description:
Let's have a coffee in Abdeen palace

Away from history which you're going to have a very delicious meal of it, but have you imagined your self having coffee in a royal palace sitting almost in the same place as the former royal family used to seat and have them coffee if not now it's the time for you to try that..

El Ismaelia is small district located between the triangle of Kasr El nile bridge, with the base of Opera square, and Ramses square it's what we call now down town or West El balad.
It was founded by Khedive Ismael after thinking alot of to change the face of Egypt to the world and that was part of his project.

For centuries Salaheddin castle was the seat of throne of the ruler of Egypt whether he's a king, or a Sultan, or a pasha but at the last quarter of the 19th century there was Khedive Ismael who decided to change the face of Cairo entirely by establishing a new seat of his throne and since that time the citadel lost almost its importance as the seat of the throne towards the new residency for the rulers of Egypt...it's called Abdeen palace.

Our tour is going to be inside the different museums of the palace:
1) The museum of the gifts received by presidents up till now;
2) The historical documents museum;
3) The silver service table settings museum;
4) The medals museum;
5) The Royal family weapons museum.


Entrance tickets: 
Egyptian:
Students: LE 10 
Adults: LE 20
Camera ticket/ cell phone with camera ticket: LE 5 
Non-Egyptian: 
Students: LE 50 
Adults: LE 100 
Camera ticket/ cell phone with camera ticket: LE 10 
Students of Archaeology, architecture, tourism guidance, Journalism , and even archaeologists, tour guides pay the entry ticket like anyone else since the palace and its museums belongs to  Presidency authority.

Food and drinks in Abdeen palace are extremely cheap so we can have a discussion after we finish our tour while having tea or coffee there :)

Felucca Trip:(optional)
After the tour, we will join a felucca for a trip on the Nile for one hour. The felucca fee is LE 40 per person; if the number of participants is less than 10, the fee may exceed LE 40 per person.

THINGS TO BRING:
1) Your personal expenses;
2) Water;
3) Hat and sunglasses;
4) Camera if you have to take photos;
5) A good mood and curiosity;

DAY RULES:
Our main ground rules are:
1) We're a community that has no color; so there's no discussion about Religion or Politics during our events;
2) We're all humans and being human is what really matters to us;
3) Everyone is welcome to join as long as s/he respects our rules;
4) Please don’t discuss controversial subjects;
5) Any form of harassment is unacceptable behavior;
6) Compliance with the general rules of behavior;
7) If you have any issues, please raise them with the organizer;
8) Suggestions are encouraged and assistance is welcomed;
9) These tours are not a venue for business development;
10) These meeting are not for dating or drinking alcohol;
11) We will listen to each other’s contributions to make it useful and free discussion is provided for at the end of the tour.

Tour guides of the Tour:
1st Muhammad Zeineddin: the first official Persian language tour guide in all A.R.E, organized 600 tours and events around Egypt, organized under the umbrella of Mosaic Club 390 events aiming to spread tolerance, speaks English, Persian and Arabic fluently, also he’s the official photographer of Mosaic Club.

Mosaic Club fees: free of charge!!
REGISTRATION IS CLOSED

Feel free to share this program with your friends
#MosaicClub #Mosaicclub_tripsandtours #Mosicclub_thehiddengemsofcairo 
Designed & organized by: 
Mosaic Club

